      "content": "It's very likely that the profile itself is acting as a proxy for deeper, unstated biases regarding their background. Judges often subconsciously associate certain environments with higher criminality, regardless of the actual facts of the drug offense. This perceived risk is less about the drug charge and more about the stereotype attached to their socio-economic status. In short, the environment is often used as a shortcut to justify harsher sentencing.",
